Strategies for benefit distribution among the cooperation enterprises in the international multimodal transport
GONG Xian－wen （Department of Economy and Business Management， Chongqing University of Education， Chongqing 400067， China） Abstract： The benefit distribution is a core problem over which each of the cooperation enterprises in the international multimodal transport shows great concern． A fair and reasonable benefit distribution mechanism is the important guarantee for international multimodal transport cooperation． On the basis of analysing the cooperation mechanism and the dynamic cooperation features of international multimodal transport， this paper uses Shapley Value method to establish the benefit distribution model， and introduces examples so as to make the distribution results more fair and reasonable． Key words： international multimodal transport； cooperation enterprise； benefit distribution； Shapley Value
